<paragraph blockId="67.[264,1323,1652,1883]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
Male. Because of its similarity to 
<taxonomicName box="[662,780,1652,1677]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Afroestricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittatus">
<emphasis box="[662,780,1652,1677]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">A. vittatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[838,962,1652,1677]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Afroestricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanfoka">
<emphasis box="[838,962,1652,1677]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">A. sanfoka</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only significant characters are included. Measurements, body 
<quantity box="[642,731,1692,1718]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" unit="mm" value="19.0">19 mm</quantity>
; wing 
<quantity box="[817,928,1692,1718]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.26" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" unit="mm" value="12.6">12.6 mm</quantity>
. FHWR 1.0:4.3; FWLR 1.0:2.0; m 
<subScript attach="both" box="[287,299,1743,1764]" fontSize="9" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">1</subScript>
WR 1.0:3.6:3.9; HFWLR 1.0:30. 
<emphasis box="[695,758,1732,1757]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Head</emphasis>
: Postocular bristles extend to midlateral margin of head. 
<emphasis box="[387,498,1777,1802]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Abdomen</emphasis>
: Apical three segments with one bristle in each apical corner. 
<emphasis box="[264,391,1817,1842]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Terminalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[407,579,1817,1843]" captionStart="FIGURES 187–192" captionStartId="68.[264,383,1095,1119]" captionTargetBox="[429,1176,447,1073]" captionTargetId="figure-231@68.[417,1191,437,1087]" captionTargetPageId="68" captionText="FIGURES 187–192. Afroestricus vorax, sp. n. Male terminalia: 187–189. Lateral, dorsal, and ventral views. 190. Gonostylus. 191–192. Aedeagus, dorsal and lateral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5050675" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5050675/files/figure.png" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Figs. 187–192</figureCitation>
): Epandrium broadly rounded apically, with a small dorsoapical notch. Gonostylus and aedeagus distinctive. Hypandrium round apically.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="68.[264,1323,284,395]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">
Female. Measurements, body 18.0 mm; wing 
<quantity box="[896,1013,284,310]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.34" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" unit="mm" value="13.4">13.4 mm</quantity>
; FHWR 1.0:4.2; FWLR 1.0:2.0; m 
<subScript attach="both" box="[385,397,335,356]" fontSize="9" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">1</subScript>
WR 1.0:4.1:4.3; HFWLR 1.0: 4.2. 
<emphasis box="[813,924,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Abdomen</emphasis>
: Terga 6 to 8 and sternum 7 with sparse, unusually stout, black bristles. 
<emphasis box="[715,843,369,394]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Terminalia</emphasis>
: Damaged, not dissected.
</paragraph>
